premise_source_doc_sentence: The phrase Zen center was coined by American students of Shunryu Suzuki in the mid-twentieth century , and the San Francisco Zen Center became the first Zen center , incorporating in 1962 .

While some are now the homes of wealthy communities in major cities  (  such as Zen Center of Los Angeles  )  , and some are in traditional mountain settings  (  such as Yokoji Zen Mountain Center  )  , other Zen centers have either humble or no permanent physical location - meeting in members private homes , university classrooms , and Quaker Meeting Houses to name but a few examples .
As Zen practice has expanded throughout the United States over the last fifty years , the variety of Zen centers has increased .
In 1970 he began his studies of Zen philosophy and Zen meditation .
After ten years of training in Zen Meditation halls , he felt that the traditional zen hall training was not helping his practice .
